label("$R$",(6,0),E);
label("$P$",(4,9),N);
label("6 cm",(3,0),S);
[/asy] The final Answer is 9
 ### Proof
 The area of a triangle can be calculated using the formula $\mbox{Area}=\frac{1}{2}\times \mbox{base} \times \mbox{height}.$ The area is $27\,\text{cm}^2$ and the base measures $6\,\text{cm}.$ Substituting these values into the formula, $$A=\frac{1}{2}\times b \times h$$becomes $$27=\frac{1}{2} \times 6 \times h$$or $27=3h.$ Therefore, $h=\boxed{9}\,\text{cm}.$
 *)

theorem
fixes base height area :: real
assumes h0 : "base = 6"
and h1 : "area = 27"
and h2 : "area = 0.5 * base * height"
shows  "height = 9"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer

